<h2 id="spotlight-link-settings" style="padding-top: 80px;">Spotlight link settings</h2>
<p>When you start typing in the Link <strong>URL</strong> field to add a link, the <strong>Link Appearance</strong> and <strong>Button colour</strong> fields will appear. Here is an explanation of the link settings fields:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Link
    <ul>
      <li><strong>URL:</strong> When you start typing in this field to add the destination for the link, the <strong>Link Appearance</strong> and <strong>Button colour</strong> fields will appear. The URL field</li>
      <li><strong>Link text:</strong> This text will appear as the Button text when "Button" is set as <strong>Link Appearance</strong>. If "Whole block" is selected, this text will be added as the "title" attribute to the whole block which is useful for screen-readers and will usually appear when a visitor hovers over the spotlight.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Link Appearance
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Button:</strong> Adds a call to action button below the other spotlight content.</li>
      <li><strong>Whole block:</strong> Makes the whole spotlight a link. The background image (if there is one) will have a zoom effect when these blocks are hovered over.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Button colour:</strong> There are 3 options for button colour:<br />
    <a class="button" href="#">Primary (black)</a> <a class="button button--secondary" href="#">Secondary (white)</a> <a class="button button--tertiary" href="#">Tertiary (orange)</a></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

