<h2 id="spotlight-display" style="padding-top: 80px;">Spotlight display</h2>
<p>This tab allows you to make visual changes to the content you have already added.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Text colour:</strong> Choose the colour of the text. It will have a drop-shadow added to help the text show up over the image. You should try to choose images well-suited to be backgrounds, i.e. No text on the image, an abstract image or one without too much detail, an image which will provide good contrast for the text.
  </li>
  <li>Display type:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Image overlay:</strong> The content will be overlaid on to an image background.</li>
      <li><strong>Image and colour block:</strong> The content will appear in a coloured block alongside an image.<br />
        The colour of the block will alternate if more than one spotlight with display type "Image and colour block" appear in the same Spotlight Group.<br />
        <strong>NOTE:</strong> Multiple spotlights added to a Spotlight Group where at least one has display type "Image and colour block" will stack on top of eachother instead of appearing alongside eachother.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Image type (only appears if "Image overlay" is selected as the <strong>Display type</strong>).
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Background image:</strong> Choose an image from the Media library or add a new image.</li>
      <li><strong>Silhouette:</strong> Choose a silhouette from the Silhouette library.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

